TITLE: Defining BaseObject Type in SDL
DESCRIPTION: Defines the root object type BaseObject with a required UUID identifier and a readonly __type__ property. The id property can be overridden by subtypes using specific UUID generation functions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/objects.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sdl
CODE:
```
abstract type std::BaseObject {
    # Universally unique object identifier
    required id: uuid {
        default := (select std::uuid_generate_v1mc());
        readonly := true;
        constraint exclusive;
    }

    # Object type in the information schema.
    required readonly __type__: schema::ObjectType;
}
```

