TITLE: Implementing RAG Endpoints in FastAPI with Gel AI (Python)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create FastAPI endpoints for fetching similar cards and querying a RAG model using the Gel AI extension. It includes methods for generating embeddings and performing semantic search.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/intro/quickstart/ai/fastapi.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import gel
import gel.ai

from fastapi import FastAPI


client = gel.create_async_client()

app = FastAPI()


@app.get("/fetch_similar")
async def fetch_similar_cards(query: str):
    rag = await gel.ai.create_async_rag_client(client, model="gpt-4-turbo-preview")
    embedding_vector = await rag.generate_embeddings(
        query, model="text-embedding-3-small"
    )

    similar_cards = await client.query(
        "select ext::ai::search(Card, <array<float32>>$embedding_vector)",
        embedding_vector=embedding_vector,
    )

    return similar_cards


@app.get("/fetch_rag")
async def fetch_rag_response(query: str):
    rag = await gel.ai.create_async_rag_client(client, model="gpt-4-turbo-preview")
    response = await rag.query_rag(
        message=query,
        context=gel.ai.QueryContext(query="select Card"),
    )
    return response
```

