TITLE: Implementing Public Visibility with Author Blocking in Gel SDL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a policy where blog posts are publicly visible except to users blocked by the author. It introduces a 'blocked' relationship in the User type and uses both allow and deny policies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/datamodel/access_policies.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: sdl
CODE:
```
type User {
  required email: str { constraint exclusive; }
  multi blocked: User;
}

type BlogPost {
  required title: str;
  required author: User;

  access policy author_has_full_access
    allow all
    using (global current_user ?= .author.id);
  access policy anyone_can_read
    allow select;
  access policy exclude_blocked
    deny select
    using ((global current_user in .author.blocked.id) ?? false);
}
```

