TITLE: Setting Vector Search Probes in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Example of using multi-statement queries to set the number of probes for approximate vector searches and then immediately perform a search. This improves the trade-off between search accuracy and performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/pgvector.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
result = client.query("""
    select set_probes(10);
    select Item { id, name }
    order by ext::pgvector::euclidean_distance(
	.embedding, <v3>$vector)
    empty last
    limit 1;
""", vector=vector)
```

