TITLE: Comparing Ranges with Greater Than Operator in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Shows how the greater than operator compares ranges and multiranges. The comparison first checks lower bounds, then upper bounds if lower bounds are equal. Unspecified upper bounds are considered greater than specified ones.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/range.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select range(1, 10) > range(2, 5);
{false}
db> select range(1, 10) > range(1, 5);
{true}
db> select range(1, 10) > range(1);
{false}
db> select range(1, 10) > range(<int64>{}, 10);
{true}

db> select multirange([range(2, 4), range(5, 7)]) >
...   multirange([range(7, 10), range(20)]);
{false}

db> select range(1, 10) > range(10, 10);
{true}
db> select range(1, 10) > range(<int64>{}, empty := true);
{true}

db> select multirange(<array<range<int64>>>[]) >
...   multirange([range(7, 10), range(20)]);
{false}
```

