TITLE: Computing Range and Multirange Intersection in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates finding the intersection of ranges and multiranges using the * operator. The result contains only the elements that are in both operands.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/range.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select range(1, 10) * range(5, 15);
{range(5, 10)}
db> select range(1, 10) * range(-15, 15);
{range(1, 10)}
db> select range(1) * range(-15, 15);
{range(1, 15)}
db> select range(10) * range(<int64>{}, 1);
{range({}, inc_lower := false, empty := true)}

db> select multirange([range(1, 10)]) *
...   multirange([range(0, 3), range(5, 6), range(9)]);
{[range(1, 3), range(5, 6), range(9, 10)]}
db> select multirange([range(2, 3), range(5, 6), range(9, 10)]) *
...   multirange([range(-10, 0), range(4, 8)]);
{[range(5, 6)]}
```

