TITLE: Using bounded_below Function in EdgeDB
DESCRIPTION: Shows usage of the bounded_below function which checks if the first range is bounded below by the lower bound of the second range. Supports both ranges and multiranges.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/range.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select bounded_below(
  range(1, 7), range(3, 6)
);
{false}
db> select bounded_below(
  range(1, 7), range(0, 6)
);
{true}

db> select bounded_below(
  multirange([
    range(-1, 0), range(5, 7),
  ]),
  multirange([
    range(1, 2), range(3, 7),
  ]),
);
{false}

db> select bounded_below(
  range(5, 7),
  multirange([
    range(1, 2), range(3, 7),
  ]),
);
{true}
```

