TITLE: Resetting Module and Alias in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates setting and resetting the default module and an alias in an EdgeQL session. It shows how to set the default module to 'foo', use it, reset it, and then how to set and reset an alias for the 'std' module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/reference/edgeql/sess_reset_alias.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
# Set the default module to "foo" for the current session.
set module foo;

# This query is now equivalent to "select foo::FooType".
select FooType;

# Reset the default module for the current session.
reset module;

# This query will now produce an error.
select FooType;

# Alias the "std" module as "foo".
set alias foo as module std;

# Now "std::min()" can be called as "foo::min()" in
# the current session.
select foo::min({1});

# Reset the alias.
reset alias foo;

# Now this query will error out, as there is no
# module "foo".
select foo::min({1});
```

