TITLE: Subtracting Ranges and Multiranges in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to perform range and multirange subtraction operations. For ranges, the result must be continuous, while multirange subtraction can result in multiple disconnected ranges.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/range.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select range(1, 10) - range(5, 15);
{range(1, 5)}
db> select range(1, 10) - range(<int64>{}, 5);
{range(5, 10)}
db> select range(1, 10) - range(0, 15);
{range({}, inc_lower := false, empty := true)}

db> select multirange([range(1, 10)]) -
...   range(4, 6);
{[range(1, 4), range(6, 10)]}
db> select multirange([range(1, 10)]) -
...   multirange([range(2, 3), range(5, 6), range(9)]);
{[range(1, 2), range(3, 5), range(6, 9)]}
db> select multirange([range(2, 3), range(5, 6), range(9, 10)]) -
...   multirange([range(-10, 0), range(4, 8)]);
{[range(2, 3), range(9, 10)]}
```

