TITLE: String Left Padding Example in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates usage of deprecated str_lpad() function for left-padding strings with spaces or custom characters. Shows truncation behavior when input exceeds target length.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/deprecated.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: edgeql-repl
CODE:
```
db> select str_lpad('short', 10);
{'     short'}
db> select str_lpad('much too long', 10);
{'much too l'}
db> select str_lpad('short', 10, '.:');
{'.:.:.short'}
```

