TITLE: Bitwise Right Shift Operation in EdgeQL
DESCRIPTION: Examples of bit_rshift() function, which performs an arithmetic right shift on an integer. Shows behavior with sign preservation and different shift amounts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/stdlib/numbers.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select bit_rshift(123, 2);
{30}
db> select bit_rshift(123, 65);
{0}
db> select bit_rshift(-123, 2);
{-31}
db> select bit_rshift(-123, 65);
{-1}
```

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select bit_rshift(bit_rshift(123, 1), 3);
{7}
db> select bit_rshift(123, 4);
{7}
db> select bit_rshift(bit_rshift(-123, 1), 3);
{-8}
db> select bit_rshift(-123, 4);
{-8}
```

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
db> select bit_rshift(123, -2);
gel error: InvalidValueError: bit_rshift(): cannot shift by
negative amount
```

