TITLE: Range Type Descriptor Structure in C
DESCRIPTION: Defines the binary structure for Range type descriptors, specifying range type information and inheritance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/resources/protocol/typedesc.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
struct RangeTypeDescriptor {
    // Indicates that this is a
    // Range Type descriptor.
    uint8   tag = 9;

    // Schema type ID.
    uuid    id;

    // Schema type name.
    string  name;

    // Whether the type is defined in the schema
    // or is ephemeral.
    bool    schema_defined;

    // Number of ancestor scalar types.
    uint16  ancestors_count;

    // Indexes of ancestor scalar type descriptors
    // in ancestor resolution order (C3).
    uint16  ancestors[ancestors_count];

    // Range type descriptor index.
    uint16  type;
};
```

