TITLE: Creating a Vector Type with Maximum Magnitude Constraint (EdgeQL)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create a Vector type with x and y properties, and a constraint ensuring the vector's magnitude is less than 5.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/reference/datamodel/constraints.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: edgeql
CODE:
```
create type Vector {
  create required property x: float64;
  create required property y: float64;
  create constraint expression ON (
    __subject__.x^2 + __subject__.y^2 < 25
  );
}
```

