TITLE: Structure Definition for std::bigint in EdgeDB Protocol
DESCRIPTION: C structure definition for std::bigint values. The structure includes fields for number of digits, weight, sign, a reserved field, and the base-10000 digits array representing the value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/geldata/gel/blob/master/docs/resources/protocol/dataformats.rst#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
struct BigInt {
    // Number of digits in digits[], can be 0.
    uint16               ndigits;

    // Weight of first digit.
    int16                weight;

    // Sign of the value
    uint16<DecimalSign>  sign;

    // Reserved value, must be zero
    uint16               reserved;

    // base-10000 digits.
    uint16                digits[ndigits];
};

enum BigIntSign {
    // Positive value.
    POS     = 0x0000;

    // Negative value.
    NEG     = 0x4000;
};
```

